	<!-- about dialog -->
	<string name="about_dialog_title">About NetSentry</string>
	<string name="about_dialog_disclaimer"><i>NetSentry</i> v%1$s</string>
	<string name="about_dialog_text"><i>NetSentry</i>
		keeps track of how much data is transferred
		over each network interface
		available to your Android system.\n

		\nThe two main screens:\n

		\n<b>The Interface List:</b>
		\nThis screen lists all active network interfaces.\n

		\n<b>The Interface Details Screen:</b>
		\nSelecting an entry from the list gives you
        detailed information about how much data has been transferred over that
        particular interface.
		
		\n
		\n<b>Miscellaneous information</b>
        \n
        \nUpdates:
        \nWhen you open <i>NetSentry</i> all data counters will be updated. 
        Automatic updates are scheduled on a regular basis. You can set the update interval using
        the preferences. 
        \n
        \nNotifications:
        \nNotifications will pop up only during automatic updates. All notifications will be cleared
        as soon as you open <i>NetSentry</i>.
	</string>

